"text-align: justify;\">These writers hoped to forge a powerful instrument to fight against the oscurantismo of the political and religious authorities. Most of the cultural and scientific figures of the time collaborated in that company, highlighting D\'Alembert, Diderot and Voltaire.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Main modern encyclopedias</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The main modern encyclopedias are:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Of Castilian speech, the Encyclopedia Espasa and the Great universal encyclopedic dictionary; both of Hispanic origin and conceived for their American and European use in the XX century.\r\nEnglish-speaking, the British Encyclopedia and the Online British Encyclopedia; encyclopedia in older English (1768). March 13 the 2012 were announced that he/she would stop to be printed and it would only be conserved the on-line version that debuted in 1994.\r\nOf French speech, the Encyclopedia Larousse (Grand Larousse) and Encyclopedia Universalis; of high recognition and published the first one for Larousse has been of great acceptance in the world.\r\nOf German speech, the Encyclopedia Brockhaus (Brockhaus Encyclopädie); the most complete in the German encyclopedias with 260.000 entrances in 17.000 pages.\r\nOf Italian speech, the Encyclopedia Treccani, the bigger than Italian origin that has 35 volumes.\r\nOf speech Portuguese, Big Portuguese enciclopédia and brasileira.\r\nOf Russian speech, the Great Soviet Encyclopedia (Bolshaya Sovietskaya Entsiklopediya); one of the most extensive publications of knowing in Slavic language.\r\nAmong the thematic ones they highlight: Encyclopedia Cattolica, New Catholic Encyclopaedia, Jewish Encyclopaedia, l\'Islam Encyclopedie and Paulys Realencyclopädie der classischen Altertumswissenschaft.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With the computer science\'s coming the encyclopedias multimedia that you/they add to the traditional information textual and pictorial audiovisual elements arise. Examples of these are British Encyclopedia, it Registers, Enciclonet and Wikipedia that can be consulted by means of optic disks or in Internet.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Characteristic of an encyclopedic text</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The encyclopedic articles present a series of characteristics that you/they distinguish them of other textual formats:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">They are very synthetic, trying to condense to the maximum the information.\r\nThey don\'t usually make concessions to the legibility of the text, prevailing the easiness of obtaining the information.\r\nExplicitan when the elements are subjective or of opinion, being prioritized the rigor and the exhibition of the facts above all.\r\nThe quantity of information that you/they contain spreads to be the possible maxim in function of the size of the work in its group.\r\nAn encyclopedia usually has several authors, being able to arrive its number to dozens and hundreds.\r\nContents of an encyclopedia</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The contents (entrances or articles) of an encyclopedia, independently of the topic that you/they try, they always complete a series of requirements:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">They are of universal interest: they can end up interesting any human being, with independence of any other consideration. This way, there are not contents of purely local or personal interest.\r\nThey are of interest atemporal: they should maintain certain interest with the step of the time, being avoided the ephemeral or fleeting information.\r\nThey are organized from the general thing to the concrete thing: this is made by the space limitations that present and to get that the complete work is self-sufficient and keep cohesion, that is to say that is not necessary to consult other texts to understand its content.\r\nThey should be the most objective possible: that is to say, in case there is diversity of focuses, or of postures, or of theories, or of opinions, to try to summarize or of mentioning all them without to take left by any, and in the event of referring to a character or a controversial situation to point out this circumstance with equanimity.\r\nThey are not a primary source of information: therefore it is convenient to indicate the or the external sources that were used.\r\nHistory</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Origins</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">An edition of Naturalis Historiæ 1669. The first publication is considered the oldest in the history.\r\nOne of the first encyclopedic works that have survived the modern times is the Naturalis History of Plinio the Old one, Roman writer of the century I D.C. He compiled a work of 37 chapters that you/they embrace the natural history of the art and the architecture, the medicine, the geography, the geology and all the aspects of the world that it surrounds him. He/she declared in the foreword that had compiled 20 thousand facts starting from 2000 diverse works of 200 authors, and he/she added that other many of their own experience. The work was published D.C. around 77 at 79, [5] although it probably never finished the work of tests before its death in the eruption of the Vesuvius in 79 D.C.</p>[:es]<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Una excursión es un recorrido o travesía, generalmente a pie, que tiene uno o más fines, que pueden ser: científicos, culturales, deportivos, educativos, militares, recreativos o turísticos con fines recreativos y deportivos a zonas naturales o rurales se le conoce como excursionismo. La persona aficionada a estas actividades se le conoce como excursionista. Se conoce también como excursionistas a quienes realizan recorridos turísticos y culturales.</p>[:]','[:en]Wellcome[:es]Bienvenido[:]','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision-v1','','','2016-06-17 00:40:20','2016-06-17 00:40:20','',4,'http://www.wowtrip.com/es/2016/06/17/4-revision-v1/',0,'revi